### SmartMoodle API — Phase 2
###
### Works with the VS Code "REST Client" extension (humao.rest-client) and
### the JetBrains HTTP client. Run the seed first:
###     docker compose exec backend npm run seed
###
### Then run the three "login as ..." requests below. The REST Client
### extension stores the JWT in @adminToken / @teacherToken / @studentToken
### automatically via the `# @name` capture, so the rest of the file works
### without manual copy/paste.

@host = http://localhost:5000
@contentType = application/json

### ===========================================================================
### 0. Health check
### ===========================================================================

### Public
GET {{host}}/health


### ===========================================================================
### 1. Auth
### ===========================================================================

### Register a new student (200/201). Re-running once gives EMAIL_TAKEN (409).
POST {{host}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "newstudent@smartmoodle.local",
  "password": "Student123!",
  "firstName": "Nouvelle",
  "lastName": "Étudiante",
  "role": "student"
}


### Register — invalid (short password) → 400 VALIDATION_ERROR
POST {{host}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "bad@smartmoodle.local",
  "password": "short",
  "firstName": "X",
  "lastName": "Y",
  "role": "student"
}


### Register — role=admin should fail (only seed creates admins) → 400
POST {{host}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "rogue@smartmoodle.local",
  "password": "Secret123!",
  "firstName": "Rogue",
  "lastName": "User",
  "role": "admin"
}


### Login as admin → captures @adminToken
# @name loginAdmin
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "admin@smartmoodle.local",
  "password": "Admin123!"
}
###
@adminToken = {{loginAdmin.response.body.token}}


### Login as teacher 1 → captures @teacherToken
# @name loginTeacher
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "teacher1@smartmoodle.local",
  "password": "Teacher123!"
}
###
@teacherToken = {{loginTeacher.response.body.token}}


### Login as a different teacher (used to test cross-teacher 403)
# @name loginTeacher2
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "teacher2@smartmoodle.local",
  "password": "Teacher123!"
}
###
@teacher2Token = {{loginTeacher2.response.body.token}}


### Login as student 1 → captures @studentToken
# @name loginStudent
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "student1@smartmoodle.local",
  "password": "Student123!"
}
###
@studentToken = {{loginStudent.response.body.token}}


### Login — wrong password → 401 INVALID_CREDENTIALS
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "student1@smartmoodle.local",
  "password": "wrong-password"
}


### GET /me — no token → 401
GET {{host}}/api/auth/me


### GET /me — malformed token → 401
GET {{host}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer not-a-real-jwt


### GET /me — valid → 200
GET {{host}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}


### ===========================================================================
### 2. Courses
### ===========================================================================

### List — no token → 401
GET {{host}}/api/courses


### List — valid (any role) → 200
GET {{host}}/api/courses
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}


### Detail — valid → 200 (course with materials array)
GET {{host}}/api/courses/1
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}


### Detail — unknown id → 404 COURSE_NOT_FOUND
GET {{host}}/api/courses/99999
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}


### Create — no token → 401
POST {{host}}/api/courses
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "Test"
}


### Create — student (wrong role) → 403 FORBIDDEN
POST {{host}}/api/courses
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "Cours interdit"
}


### Create — teacher → 201
# @name createCourse
POST {{host}}/api/courses
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "Cours d'essai - API HTTP",
  "description": "Créé via le client HTTP."
}
###
@newCourseId = {{createCourse.response.body.course.id}}


### Update — owner teacher → 200
PUT {{host}}/api/courses/{{newCourseId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "description": "Description mise à jour."
}


### Update — different teacher (not owner, not admin) → 403
PUT {{host}}/api/courses/{{newCourseId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{teacher2Token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "Tentative interdite"
}


### Update — admin can update any course → 200
PUT {{host}}/api/courses/{{newCourseId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "Renommé par admin"
}


### List students of a course — no token → 401
GET {{host}}/api/courses/1/students


### List students — student role → 403
GET {{host}}/api/courses/1/students
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}


### List students — teacher who is NOT the owner → 403
GET {{host}}/api/courses/1/students
Authorization: Bearer {{teacher2Token}}


### List students — owner teacher → 200
GET {{host}}/api/courses/1/students
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}


### List students — admin → 200
GET {{host}}/api/courses/1/students
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}


### Delete — different teacher → 403
DELETE {{host}}/api/courses/{{newCourseId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{teacher2Token}}


### Delete — owner teacher → 204
DELETE {{host}}/api/courses/{{newCourseId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}


### ===========================================================================
### 3. Enrollments
### ===========================================================================

### Enroll — no token → 401
POST {{host}}/api/enrollments
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{ "courseId": 1 }


### Enroll — teacher (wrong role) → 403
POST {{host}}/api/enrollments
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{ "courseId": 1 }


### Enroll — student into a new course → 201
POST {{host}}/api/enrollments
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{ "courseId": 2 }


### Enroll — same student again into same course → 409 ALREADY_ENROLLED
POST {{host}}/api/enrollments
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{ "courseId": 2 }


### Enroll — non-existent course → 404 COURSE_NOT_FOUND
POST {{host}}/api/enrollments
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{ "courseId": 99999 }


### My enrollments — no token → 401
GET {{host}}/api/enrollments/me


### My enrollments — teacher (wrong role) → 403
GET {{host}}/api/enrollments/me
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}


### My enrollments — student → 200
GET {{host}}/api/enrollments/me
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}


### ===========================================================================
### 4. Admin
### ===========================================================================

### List users — no token → 401
GET {{host}}/api/admin/users


### List users — student → 403
GET {{host}}/api/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}


### List users — teacher → 403
GET {{host}}/api/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}


### List users — admin → 200
GET {{host}}/api/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}


### Change role — student attempting → 403
PATCH {{host}}/api/admin/users/4/role
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{ "role": "teacher" }


### Change role — admin promotes a student to teacher → 200
PATCH {{host}}/api/admin/users/4/role
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{ "role": "teacher" }


### Change role — admin demotes back to student → 200
PATCH {{host}}/api/admin/users/4/role
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{ "role": "student" }


### Change role — invalid role → 400
PATCH {{host}}/api/admin/users/4/role
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{ "role": "wizard" }


### Delete user — student attempting → 403
DELETE {{host}}/api/admin/users/5
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}


### Delete user — admin trying to delete self → 400 CANNOT_DELETE_SELF
### (replace the id below with the admin id from /api/admin/users)
DELETE {{host}}/api/admin/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}


### Delete user — admin deletes the previously-registered "newstudent" → 204
### (find the id via GET /api/admin/users and update the URL accordingly)
# DELETE {{host}}/api/admin/users/8
# Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}


### ===========================================================================
### 5. Course materials (Phase 3 — PDF upload via Google Drive)
### ===========================================================================
### Drop a PDF at backend/test-files/sample.pdf before running these.
### REST Client: the `< ./path` syntax inlines a file's contents.

### Upload — no token → 401
POST {{host}}/api/courses/1/materials
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----Form

------Form
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="title"

Should fail
------Form
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./test-files/sample.pdf
------Form--


### Upload — student (wrong role) → 403
POST {{host}}/api/courses/1/materials
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----Form

------Form
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="title"

Should fail
------Form
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./test-files/sample.pdf
------Form--


### Upload — wrong teacher (not the owner) → 403
POST {{host}}/api/courses/1/materials
Authorization: Bearer {{teacher2Token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----Form

------Form
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="title"

Should fail
------Form
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./test-files/sample.pdf
------Form--


### Upload — non-PDF mime → 400 INVALID_FILE_TYPE
POST {{host}}/api/courses/1/materials
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----Form

------Form
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="title"

Bad type
------Form
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="image.png"
Content-Type: image/png

< ./test-files/sample.pdf
------Form--


### Upload — owner teacher with valid PDF → 201
# @name uploadMaterial
POST {{host}}/api/courses/1/materials
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="title"

Cours d'introduction (PDF)
--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./test-files/sample.pdf
--boundary--

###

@materialId = {{uploadMaterial.response.body.material.id}}

###
### List materials of a course — no token → 401
GET {{host}}/api/courses/1/materials


### List materials — student NOT enrolled in this course → 403
### (use a token for a student who is not enrolled in course 1)
GET {{host}}/api/courses/2/materials
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}


### List materials — enrolled student → 200
GET {{host}}/api/courses/1/materials
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}


### List materials — owner teacher → 200
GET {{host}}/api/courses/1/materials
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}


### List materials — admin → 200
GET {{host}}/api/courses/1/materials
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}


### Download — no token → 401
GET {{host}}/api/materials/{{materialId}}/download


### Download — non-enrolled student → 403
### (use a course/student combination where the student is NOT enrolled)
GET {{host}}/api/materials/{{materialId}}/download
Authorization: Bearer {{teacher2Token}}


### Download — enrolled student → 200 (binary PDF stream)
GET {{host}}/api/materials/{{materialId}}/download
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}


### Delete — student → 403
DELETE {{host}}/api/materials/{{materialId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}


### Delete — different teacher → 403
DELETE {{host}}/api/materials/{{materialId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{teacher2Token}}


### Delete — owner teacher → 204 (also removes the Drive file)
DELETE {{host}}/api/materials/{{materialId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}


### Delete — already-deleted material → 404 MATERIAL_NOT_FOUND
DELETE {{host}}/api/materials/{{materialId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}


### ===========================================================================
### 6. Quizzes (Phase 4 — AI-generated MCQ from PDF + adaptive taking flow)
### ===========================================================================
### Pre-requisite: a PDF has been uploaded (run the upload block in section 5
### first and reuse @materialId). Gemini env vars must be set.

### Generate quiz — no token → 401
POST {{host}}/api/materials/{{materialId}}/generate-quiz
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{}


### Generate quiz — student (wrong role) → 403
POST {{host}}/api/materials/{{materialId}}/generate-quiz
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{}


### Generate quiz — non-owner teacher → 403
POST {{host}}/api/materials/{{materialId}}/generate-quiz
Authorization: Bearer {{teacher2Token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{}


### Generate quiz — owner teacher, default mix (4/4/2) → 201 (10–30 s)
# @name generateQuiz
POST {{host}}/api/materials/{{materialId}}/generate-quiz
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{}
###
@quizId = {{generateQuiz.response.body.quiz.id}}


### Generate quiz — custom mix → 201
POST {{host}}/api/materials/{{materialId}}/generate-quiz
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "numEasy": 3,
  "numMedium": 3,
  "numHard": 2
}


### Generate quiz — invalid counts (total 0) → 400
POST {{host}}/api/materials/{{materialId}}/generate-quiz
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "numEasy": 0,
  "numMedium": 0,
  "numHard": 0
}


### Get quiz — student, is_correct stripped → 200
GET {{host}}/api/quizzes/{{quizId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}


### Get quiz — owner teacher, full answers → 200
GET {{host}}/api/quizzes/{{quizId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}


### List quizzes for a course — enrolled student → 200
GET {{host}}/api/courses/1/quizzes
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}


### Start a quiz — teacher (wrong role) → 403
POST {{host}}/api/quizzes/{{quizId}}/start
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}


### Start a quiz — non-enrolled student → 403
POST {{host}}/api/quizzes/{{quizId}}/start
Authorization: Bearer {{teacher2Token}}


### Start a quiz — enrolled student → 201
# @name startAttempt
POST {{host}}/api/quizzes/{{quizId}}/start
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}

@attemptId = {{startAttempt.response.body.attempt.id}}
@firstQuestionId = {{startAttempt.response.body.question.id}}
@firstAnswerId = {{startAttempt.response.body.question.answers.0.id}}


### Answer a question — no token → 401
POST {{host}}/api/attempts/{{attemptId}}/answer
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{ "questionId": {{firstQuestionId}}, "selectedAnswerId": {{firstAnswerId}} }


### Answer — wrong student → 403
POST {{host}}/api/attempts/{{attemptId}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{teacher2Token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{ "questionId": {{firstQuestionId}}, "selectedAnswerId": {{firstAnswerId}} }


### Answer — invalid (mismatched question/answer) → 400
POST {{host}}/api/attempts/{{attemptId}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{ "questionId": {{firstQuestionId}}, "selectedAnswerId": 999999 }


### Answer — owner student, first question → 200 (next question included)
# @name answer1
POST {{host}}/api/attempts/{{attemptId}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{ "questionId": {{firstQuestionId}}, "selectedAnswerId": {{firstAnswerId}} }
###
@nextQuestionId = {{answer1.response.body.nextQuestion.id}}
###
@nextAnswerId = {{answer1.response.body.nextQuestion.answers.0.id}}


### Answer — duplicate question → 409 QUESTION_ALREADY_ANSWERED
POST {{host}}/api/attempts/{{attemptId}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{ "questionId": {{firstQuestionId}}, "selectedAnswerId": {{firstAnswerId}} }


### Answer — keep going (repeat manually until isComplete=true)
POST {{host}}/api/attempts/{{attemptId}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{ "questionId": {{nextQuestionId}}, "selectedAnswerId": {{nextAnswerId}} }


### Result — student owner → 200 (full breakdown with correct answers)
GET {{host}}/api/attempts/{{attemptId}}/result
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}


### Result — owner teacher → 200
GET {{host}}/api/attempts/{{attemptId}}/result
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}


### Result — different teacher → 403
GET {{host}}/api/attempts/{{attemptId}}/result
Authorization: Bearer {{teacher2Token}}


### Result — different student → 403
GET {{host}}/api/attempts/{{attemptId}}/result
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}


### ===========================================================================
### 7. Rate limiter sanity check
### ===========================================================================
### Fire this >10 times in 15 minutes from the same IP to see 429 RATE_LIMITED
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "nobody@smartmoodle.local",
  "password": "wrong"
}
